   "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
   "body" : "This PR enables one more of the non-wallet functional tests (p2p_segwit.py) to be run even with the Bitcoin Code wallet by using the MiniWallet instead, as proposed in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/20078.\r\n\r\nThis change only affects the subtest `test_superfluous_witness`. Note that instead of creating a raw transaction first and then signing it, we go the other direction here: MiniWallet creates a transaction spending a segwit v1 output (i.e. including a witness), then we turn it into a raw transaction by dropping the witness. Therefore, the debug log asserts are swapped.",
